                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 18: The department of telecom (DoT) is understood to be exploring the option of selecting four mobile number portability operators on a regional basis as opposed to the The Telecom Regulatory Authority of Indias (Trai) recommendation of a single centralised agency for offering number portability solutions in the country. Trai had forwarded to DoT the draft request for proposal for the selection of a single operator, which would be licensed to provide and operate end-to-end mobile number portability solution in the country.                             
	 Mumbai, May 18: Steel prices are expected to remain firm in 2008 as supply side constraints continue to persist with major greenfield projects hitting roadblocks because of delays in acquiring land.                            
	 New Delhi, May 18: Assocham has said the government must remove investment hurdles in the industry and farm sectors besides easing the tax burden on households to 20 per cent to ensure 12 per cent growth in the manufacturing sector this fiscal.                            
	 hyderabad, may 18: nmdc has registered a profit after tax of rs 3,250.98 crore for the year ended march 31 against Rs 2,320.21 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal, a growth of 40.12 per cent.                            
	 Mumbai, May 18: lanco Infratech, the flagship company of Hyderabad-based Lanco Group, is in talks with a couple of overseas private equity players to raise $200 million for its realty business.                                                                                                                         
